{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin with a manifest missing a required field is rejected before any plugin code executes.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is between manifest validation and loader execution gating (MOCK-MISS): a unit test of schema validation alone cannot prove the loader avoids importing/executing the plugin. Minimum real setup is multiple local modules plus plugin fixture files to observe import side effects. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess requirement beyond normal in-process file/module wiring, so not System; (b) no AI output dependency; (c) no multi-agent chain. REJECTION-GATE: rejected System because behavior text only requires rejection before execution, not subprocess/real network/OS-event behavior.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one invalid `manifest.json` and an entry module that writes a sentinel when imported. Run the real loader against that directory; assert loader reports manifest validation failure, sentinel was not written, and `onLoad` was never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"If plugin A depends on plugin B, `onLoad` for B runs before `onLoad` for A.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at module handoff between dependency resolver and hook invoker (MOCK-MISS). A pure unit test of topological sort can miss wrong call sequencing in loader orchestration. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no real OS/network/subprocess dependency, no AI dependency, no agentic chain. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Unit because behavior text is about actual `onLoad` invocation order, not only graph algorithm output.","test_description":"Set up two plugin fixtures where A declares dependency on B; each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory/event log. Execute loader and assert log order is `[B