l,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If a plugin throws during `onLoad`, loader continues initializing other plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration/state-propagation across dependency graph and error handling paths (MOCK-MISS). Unit testing exception handling in one function cannot verify selective continuation vs skip behavior across multiple plugins. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no real OS/network/subprocess needed; no AI output quality dependence; no multi-agent sequence. REJECTION-GATE: rejected System because behavior text concerns loader control flow, not external infra behavior.","test_description":"Create plugins: `X` throws in `onLoad`, `Y` independent, `Z` depends on `X`. Run loader and assert `Y` still loads, `Z` does not load, and error for `X` is reported without aborting whole initialization.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}}]}
